# Cursor Rules for StreamTeX Project

## File Extension Standards
All rule files must use the `.mdc` extension. See: [.cursor/rules/file-extension-standards.mdc](.cursor/rules/file-extension-standards.mdc)

## Project-Specific Rules
See: [.cursor/rules/streamtex/streamtex-project-rules.mdc](.cursor/rules/streamtex/streamtex-project-rules.mdc)

## General Development Rules
- Follow Python PEP 8 style guidelines
- Use type hints where appropriate
- Write clear, descriptive variable and function names
- Add docstrings for all public functions and classes
- Keep functions focused and single-purpose
- Use meaningful commit messages
- Test code before committing
